3
00:01:12.319 --> 00:01:15.319
(All characters. locations. organizations. religions.)

4
00:01:15.319 --> 00:01:17.858
(and incidents in this drama are fictional.)

5
00:01:18.724 --> 00:01:21.763
(Episode 11)

6
00:01:23.693 --> 00:01:26.103
Tell me everything.

7
00:01:34.203 --> 00:01:36.813
Tell me. Dong Kyung.

8
00:01:45.854 --> 00:01:47.053
I want to live.

9
00:01:49.854 --> 00:01:51.154
I really...

10
00:01:54.623 --> 00:01:56.693
I really. really want to live.

11
00:02:01.104 --> 00:02:02.203
I...

12
00:02:05.273 --> 00:02:08.504
I want to live with you. Sun Kyung.

13
00:02:09.844 --> 00:02:12.913
my aunt. Ji Na.

14
00:02:14.913 --> 00:02:17.713
and everyone else that I love.

15
00:02:19.153 --> 00:02:20.224
I really do.

16
00:02:22.823 --> 00:02:24.624
I really want...

17
00:02:25.293 --> 00:02:27.594
I want to live so badly.

18
00:02:40.144 --> 00:02:41.174
Me too.

19
00:02:42.743 --> 00:02:43.974
Me too. Dong Kyung.

20
00:02:53.683 --> 00:02:55.023
I want to be alive...

21
00:02:57.193 --> 00:02:58.553
so I can...

22
00:03:03.293 --> 00:03:04.864
So I can die with you.

23
00:03:37.394 --> 00:03:39.164
When Sun Kyung and I were young.

24
00:03:39.164 --> 00:03:40.764
he asked me where our parents had gone.

25
00:03:40.764 --> 00:03:42.364
I told him that they were up there.

26
00:03:43.204 --> 00:03:45.003
But when he asked me why they had left.

27
00:03:45.574 --> 00:03:47.273
I had nothing to tell him.

28
00:03:48.873 --> 00:03:51.414
So one day. I sat here to no end.

29
00:03:54.313 --> 00:03:56.484
When I kept staring at the sky. I realized it.

30
00:03:57.653 --> 00:04:00.424
We all go back to where we came from.

31
00:04:03.294 --> 00:04:05.053
People say that our bodies come from the stars...

32
00:04:05.993 --> 00:04:09.563
because all the energy that make up our bodies is from the stars.

33
00:04:10.593 --> 00:04:14.634
So when we go back. deeper and deeper into the past.

34
00:04:16.063 --> 00:04:18.174
we basically originate from the same place.

35
00:04:19.674 --> 00:04:21.243
We all go back to the same place...

36
00:04:24.514 --> 00:04:26.243
and meet there again.

37
00:04:39.093 --> 00:04:40.894
So we will never be apart.

38
00:05:38.384 --> 00:05:39.554
Hey!

39
00:05:39.754 --> 00:05:41.084
Bring Lee Hyun here right now.

40
00:05:41.084 --> 00:05:42.324
Make her apologize.

41
00:05:43.423 --> 00:05:44.824
Where's Mr. Cha?

42
00:05:44.824 --> 00:05:45.923
Mr. Cha!

43
00:05:46.363 --> 00:05:48.494
- Where is he? He should be working. - He's working outside the office.

44
00:05:48.863 --> 00:05:49.963
Call him.

45
00:05:50.463 --> 00:05:51.593
Gosh.

46
00:05:55.934 --> 00:05:58.533
I heard that you made the situation worse.

47
00:05:58.874 --> 00:06:00.244
He was about to go and see a plastic surgeon.

48
00:06:00.244 --> 00:06:01.543
I barely managed to stop him.

49
00:06:02.244 --> 00:06:04.213
- Why did you do that? - Why did I...

50
00:06:05.014 --> 00:06:08.113
Hey. our company will go bankrupt with him.

51
00:06:08.514 --> 00:06:09.983
If losing a writer would bankrupt the company.

52
00:06:09.983 --> 00:06:11.384
the company was bound to fail then.

53
00:06:11.384 --> 00:06:12.454
Hey!

54
00:06:14.423 --> 00:06:16.353
"Hey." "You." "That." "This."

55
00:06:16.694 --> 00:06:18.423
I told you not to address people like that.

56
00:06:20.293 --> 00:06:22.194
Anyway. call Lee Hyun right now.

57
00:06:22.194 --> 00:06:24.593
If she can't apologize. pay for the laptop. at least.

58
00:06:25.093 --> 00:06:26.764
Just deduct it from my pay.

59
00:06:26.764 --> 00:06:27.804
Your pay?

60
00:06:28.033 --> 00:06:30.533
Gosh. You don't even make that much money. It's chicken feed.

61
00:06:30.533 --> 00:06:32.634
So you know that what you pay me is chicken feed.

62
00:06:34.343 --> 00:06:36.944
You think this job is easy because you get paid...

63
00:06:36.944 --> 00:06:38.413
every month without doing so much.

64
00:06:38.413 --> 00:06:40.043
Go check out the job market.

65
00:06:40.043 --> 00:06:41.983
There's a line of people...

66
00:06:41.983 --> 00:06:44.113
who are willing to work for your chicken feed.

67
00:06:44.713 --> 00:06:47.353
Seriously. Kids these days have no love for their company.

68
00:06:47.653 --> 00:06:49.483
You should treat the company as yours...

69
00:06:49.483 --> 00:06:51.824
and work as if you're running your own business.

70
00:06:51.824 --> 00:06:53.124
You should be frugal like you are with your own money.

71
00:06:53.124 --> 00:06:55.723
How can I treat it as my company when it's not?

72
00:06:58.233 --> 00:07:00.663
You're not successful because of that attitude.

73
00:07:01.134 --> 00:07:02.163
Mr. Cha.

74
00:07:02.663 --> 00:07:04.334
Don't you want to be more like me?

75
00:07:04.704 --> 00:07:07.374
Do you want to end your life after earning...

76
00:07:07.374 --> 00:07:08.704
that chicken feed all your life?

77
00:07:12.473 --> 00:07:15.113
Gosh. I can't put up with this ridiculous job.

78
00:07:15.113 --> 00:07:17.054
- What? - I can't put up with this dumb job.

79
00:07:17.483 --> 00:07:19.454
I'm sure you know what I mean by that.

80
00:07:22.324 --> 00:07:23.593
I'm quitting.

81
00:07:23.593 --> 00:07:25.324
Deduct the laptop price from my severance pay.

82
00:07:25.593 --> 00:07:28.663
My gosh. Your severance pay isn't even that much.

83
00:07:28.994 --> 00:07:32.293
Hey. I've lived my life 10 more years than you.

84
00:07:32.293 --> 00:07:34.204
I've seen a lot of guys...

85
00:07:34.204 --> 00:07:35.903
ruining their lives because of their petty pride.

86
00:07:35.903 --> 00:07:37.634
Since you're the team leader here.

87
00:07:37.634 --> 00:07:39.304
you must think other companies would hire you.

88
00:07:39.773 --> 00:07:43.473
Listen. young man. The world out there is a tough place.

89
00:07:43.473 --> 00:07:45.744
You have a long way of saying that you're a dinosaur.

90
00:07:46.584 --> 00:07:47.713
Hey. Cha Joo Ik.

91
00:07:50.954 --> 00:07:52.014
Are you really quitting?

92
00:07:52.014 --> 00:07:53.684
What are you going to do with your life then?

93
00:07:54.324 --> 00:07:57.593
Seriously. People might think your dad owns several buildings.

94
00:07:59.093 --> 00:08:01.163
What? How did you know that?

95
00:08:01.463 --> 00:08:02.523
What?

96
00:08:04.733 --> 00:08:06.264
My dad owns buildings.

97
00:08:06.963 --> 00:08:08.004
This building. too.

98
00:08:14.144 --> 00:08:16.444
Ji Na came here on her school trip.

99
00:08:16.613 --> 00:08:18.014
Remember the hotel we passed by on our way here?

100
00:08:18.014 --> 00:08:19.314
That's where she stayed.

101
00:08:19.574 --> 00:08:22.814
I was doing my side job to make some pocket money.

102
00:08:23.454 --> 00:08:24.584
What was the side job?

103
00:08:25.783 --> 00:08:26.824
It was just a job.

104
00:08:27.023 --> 00:08:29.923
It was a way to make memories when I was in school.

105
00:08:30.994 --> 00:08:32.523
Gosh. It was a good side job.

106
00:08:33.163 --> 00:08:35.023
I had never seen anyone jump over the wall...

107
00:08:35.023 --> 00:08:36.163
as cool as she did.

108
00:08:36.163 --> 00:08:38.264
She said that she liked me when we first met.

109
00:08:38.264 --> 00:08:40.403
What did she like about you?

110
00:08:41.713 --> 00:08:43.422
She liked me for my bubbly personality.

111
00:08:43.577 --> 00:08:46.887
Anyway. we exchanged numbers and stayed in touch.

112
00:08:46.887 --> 00:08:49.247
And she told me to apply to her school.

113
00:08:49.247 --> 00:08:50.786
But don't you know how smart I am?

114
00:08:50.786 --> 00:08:52.656
And I got into her school just like that.

115
00:08:55.426 --> 00:08:57.397
Our food is here.

116
00:08:59.897 --> 00:09:00.966
This is great.

117
00:09:05.166 --> 00:09:07.337
It looks delicious. Thank you for the food.

118
00:09:21.346 --> 00:09:22.416
Look at you eat.

119
00:09:22.916 --> 00:09:24.356
Do you know how many times Sun Kyung changed his mind...

120
00:09:24.356 --> 00:09:25.387
on what he wanted to become?

121
00:09:25.387 --> 00:09:26.486
One day. he wants to become this.

122
00:09:26.486 --> 00:09:28.027
The next day. he wants to become something else.

123
00:09:28.027 --> 00:09:30.457
But you know what's funny? He means it every time.

124
00:09:30.897 --> 00:09:33.796
And in the end. I'm the one who deals with it.

125
00:09:33.796 --> 00:09:37.267
Sun Kyung would go to internet cafés after telling me he's off to study.

126
00:09:37.267 --> 00:09:39.467
My job was to go around looking for him.

127
00:09:40.107 --> 00:09:42.367
It's like everyone in your family either chases or gets chased.

128
00:09:42.637 --> 00:09:44.906
The one getting chased always ends up getting caught.

129
00:09:44.906 --> 00:09:46.977
You saw how my aunt caught me by my collar. right?

130
00:09:46.977 --> 00:09:49.206
As for me. I used to drag Sun Kyung by his ear.

131
00:09:56.416 --> 00:09:58.416
Hello!

132
00:10:00.426 --> 00:10:01.456
Hi.

133
00:10:10.367 --> 00:10:11.367
What?

134
00:10:11.867 --> 00:10:12.897
It's nothing.

135
00:10:15.943 --> 00:10:17.836
When my aunt and uncle were dating.

136
00:10:17.836 --> 00:10:20.377
they ran into Sun Kyung on a path like this.

137
00:10:20.706 --> 00:10:22.406
Sun Kyung called me that day...

138
00:10:22.406 --> 00:10:25.316
and cried his eyes out saying we lost our aunt forever.

139
00:10:25.747 --> 00:10:27.517
So do you know what I did?

140
00:10:28.517 --> 00:10:29.786
I looked for a job.

141
00:10:30.117 --> 00:10:32.086
I figured I should hurry up and start making money...

142
00:10:32.086 --> 00:10:34.426
in order to help my aunt get married quickly.

143
00:10:34.426 --> 00:10:35.887
I started working at the publishing company...

144
00:10:35.887 --> 00:10:36.997
because they called me first.

145
00:10:36.997 --> 00:10:38.696
But I had no idea I'd end up working there for so long.

146
00:10:39.497 --> 00:10:40.597
What does your earning money...

147
00:10:40.597 --> 00:10:42.097
have anything to do with your aunt getting married?

148
00:10:42.166 --> 00:10:44.436
I had to have the ability to earn money...

149
00:10:44.436 --> 00:10:47.036
so my aunt would feel at ease and live her own life...

150
00:10:47.166 --> 00:10:48.706
thinking I was all grown up.

151
00:10:49.336 --> 00:10:51.936
Otherwise. she would've spent her entire life looking after us.

152
00:10:52.836 --> 00:10:55.747
So tell me. Are you all grown up?

153
00:11:16.326 --> 00:11:19.467
No. I'm still growing up.

154
00:11:41.956 --> 00:11:44.826
I'm no longer alone.

155
00:12:11.586 --> 00:12:13.757
I once saw a dolphin here.

156
00:12:14.757 --> 00:12:18.357
Later on. I found out it was an Indo-Pacific bottlenose dolphin.

157
00:12:18.357 --> 00:12:21.597
They're an endangered species. Isn't that sad?

158
00:12:23.436 --> 00:12:25.696
I can't say that's not my fault.

159
00:12:26.367 --> 00:12:28.267
but you humans need to work on it too.

160
00:12:29.237 --> 00:12:32.176
Yes. you're right. It's our fault.

161
00:12:32.836 --> 00:12:34.946
But for your information. I wasn't blaming you.

162
00:12:36.977 --> 00:12:38.647
Why are you laughing?

163
00:12:38.647 --> 00:12:39.676
Because I find it funny.

164
00:12:39.877 --> 00:12:41.617
What's so funny?

165
00:12:42.446 --> 00:12:43.556
You.

166
00:12:43.556 --> 00:12:46.286
What's so funny about me?

167
00:12:48.286 --> 00:12:50.296
What's funny about me?

168
00:12:57.536 --> 00:13:00.566
We're heading somewhere together.

169
00:13:03.507 --> 00:13:06.176
As we sympathize with and love each other.

170
00:13:06.877 --> 00:13:07.977
We're in this together.

171
00:13:29.127 --> 00:13:30.166
Is something bothering you?

172
00:14:06.980 --> 00:14:08.081
How about a bet?

173
00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:11.780
The winner gets to ask for whatever he wants from the other person.

174
00:14:12.380 --> 00:14:14.691
- What do you want? - Your car.

175
00:14:18.020 --> 00:14:19.020
Or...

176
00:14:21.161 --> 00:14:22.230
maybe something else.

177
00:14:25.061 --> 00:14:26.061
Sure. Let's do it.

178
00:15:08.610 --> 00:15:09.610
Tell me.

179
00:15:10.411 --> 00:15:11.510
What do you want?

180
00:15:12.441 --> 00:15:13.551
I'll save it.

181
00:15:14.280 --> 00:15:17.221
I'll tell you once there's something I want.

182
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:20.650
Why? Don't you want anything from me yet?

183
00:15:50.480 --> 00:15:51.951
You asked for my car. right?

184
00:15:55.390 --> 00:15:56.591
You can have it.

185
00:15:59.990 --> 00:16:02.091
Don't give it to me like you're being nice.

186
00:16:05.431 --> 00:16:06.831
I'm going to win it.

187
00:16:25.520 --> 00:16:26.551
I'll save it.

188
00:16:26.921 --> 00:16:30.291
I'll tell you once there's something I want.

189
00:16:32.620 --> 00:16:33.691
Welcome...

190
00:16:41.030 --> 00:16:42.071
Let's go on a date.

191
00:16:43.600 --> 00:16:46.471
- What? - Let's go on three dates.

192
00:16:48.211 --> 00:16:49.510
I want to know if these are just lingering feelings...

193
00:16:49.510 --> 00:16:50.640
or if I actually still like you.

194
00:16:51.211 --> 00:16:53.110
Let's decide after three dates.

195
00:16:57.721 --> 00:16:59.650
- Sure. - Don't ever call me first.

196
00:16:59.650 --> 00:17:01.191
And don't visit without calling.

197
00:17:01.890 --> 00:17:02.890
Okay.

198
00:17:03.191 --> 00:17:05.161
I'll be the one to call. so wait until I do.

199
00:17:05.760 --> 00:17:07.230
Okay. I will.

200
00:17:08.091 --> 00:17:10.400
- It might take some time. - I'll still wait.

201
00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:12.561
I'm going to go now.

202
00:17:17.541 --> 00:17:19.000
I'm going to wait. okay?

203
00:17:35.191 --> 00:17:36.850
- Hello? - I just asked Hyun Kyu...

204
00:17:36.850 --> 00:17:38.721
to go on a date with me.

205
00:18:01.280 --> 00:18:03.181
Let's cancel our contract.

206
00:18:04.221 --> 00:18:06.351
Don't worry. You won't have to pay a penalty.

207
00:18:06.881 --> 00:18:08.820
I'm guessing you won't want to see me again.

208
00:18:09.621 --> 00:18:12.121
You won't ever see me again because of work.

209
00:18:13.361 --> 00:18:14.391
No.

210
00:18:16.961 --> 00:18:18.101
Why?

211
00:18:18.101 --> 00:18:19.931
Because I want my novel to fall into the top 10.

212
00:18:21.371 --> 00:18:22.401
Is that the only reason?

213
00:18:24.740 --> 00:18:25.740
Yes.

214
00:18:29.171 --> 00:18:31.540
Then either email me or text me.

215
00:18:32.141 --> 00:18:34.050
If you break our contract.

216
00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:39.550
I'm going to tell Hyun Kyu that you kissed me.

217
00:18:40.250 --> 00:18:42.250
- Can you really do that? - Do you think I won't be able to?

218
00:18:42.250 --> 00:18:44.461
I don't think you can.

219
00:18:46.221 --> 00:18:48.391
If you can. go ahead and tell him.

220
00:18:52.230 --> 00:18:53.230
Seriously.

221
00:18:54.270 --> 00:18:55.371
He's so annoying.

222
00:19:10.050 --> 00:19:12.320
Make sure you don't get exposed to these elements.

223
00:19:26.661 --> 00:19:27.671
What is it?

224
00:19:29.406 --> 00:19:30.476
What?

225
00:19:31.300 --> 00:19:34.310
I'm coming. Fine. I'll be right there.

226
00:19:44.080 --> 00:19:46.181
My aunt left my place as is.

227
00:19:46.351 --> 00:19:48.351
She says I need a place to return to.

228
00:19:49.550 --> 00:19:52.060
I didn't know I'd end up coming here with you though.

229
00:20:09.773 --> 00:20:10.912
I have a wish.

230
00:20:12.082 --> 00:20:13.082
A wish?

231
00:20:13.713 --> 00:20:16.612
- My birthday wish. - That's...

232
00:20:16.882 --> 00:20:19.582
Not the one I made then. Something else.

233
00:20:23.323 --> 00:20:25.362
- Forgive me. - For what?

234
00:20:35.733 --> 00:20:38.372
I told them that you were here.

235
00:20:41.099 --> 00:20:42.798
I thought they'd worry.

236
00:20:43.243 --> 00:20:44.243
Dong Kyung!

237
00:20:44.983 --> 00:20:47.513
What? Let go!

238
00:20:49.953 --> 00:20:50.953
Darn it.

239
00:20:56.453 --> 00:20:57.463
Auntie.

240
00:21:17.142 --> 00:21:19.043
Let's eat. I'm hungry.

241
00:21:46.660 --> 00:21:48.759
I asked you out here because I wanted to talk to you.

242
00:21:49.289 --> 00:21:52.230
I think I must be a real coward.

243
00:21:52.900 --> 00:21:55.430
Jeju is beautiful. Look at the sea.

244
00:21:57.400 --> 00:21:59.870
I couldn't even run away for real.

245
00:21:59.870 --> 00:22:01.870
All I did was hurt everyone.

246
00:22:03.440 --> 00:22:04.910
This is where I got my family.

247
00:22:07.610 --> 00:22:09.880
I don't know what to do.

248
00:22:10.980 --> 00:22:12.780
If I live. he dies.

249
00:22:13.051 --> 00:22:15.581
If I save him. we all die.

250
00:22:16.851 --> 00:22:18.151
What should I do?

251
00:22:19.121 --> 00:22:20.891
What do I do?

252
00:22:22.020 --> 00:22:23.131
"What do I do?"

253
00:22:24.361 --> 00:22:26.661
Don't worry. We're family.

254
00:22:26.801 --> 00:22:29.030
I want you to think of me as family and lean on me.

255
00:22:30.530 --> 00:22:33.000
- Family? - Yes. family.

256
00:22:33.801 --> 00:22:35.000
I know how you feel.

257
00:22:35.470 --> 00:22:37.571
Let me do my best to find a great hospital.

258
00:22:38.740 --> 00:22:41.980
The best option was for me to die by myself.

259
00:22:42.841 --> 00:22:45.151
That was why I came here.

260
00:22:46.351 --> 00:22:48.780
But I can't not love. Kevin.

261
00:22:48.780 --> 00:22:50.051
I love you too. Dong Kyung.

262
00:22:51.851 --> 00:22:53.361
I love everything Soo loves.

263
00:22:53.720 --> 00:22:56.530
Just hang in there. Everything is going to be better.

264
00:22:58.131 --> 00:22:59.161
Love.

265
00:22:59.631 --> 00:23:02.361
Yes. That's what scares me.

266
00:23:03.401 --> 00:23:06.601
My love is too burdensome.

267
00:23:06.841 --> 00:23:07.970
You're welcome.

268
00:23:07.970 --> 00:23:09.841
Family doesn't have to say. "Thank you."

269
00:23:09.841 --> 00:23:11.010
"I love you" is enough.

270
00:23:34.401 --> 00:23:35.831
Doctor.

271
00:23:37.301 --> 00:23:41.000
Would you get me the onions from those groceries over there?

272
00:23:51.280 --> 00:23:53.780
Wash them over here.

273
00:24:06.331 --> 00:24:07.401
Thank you...

274
00:24:08.734 --> 00:24:09.893
for telling me.

275
00:24:10.331 --> 00:24:11.631
I thought you'd worry.

276
00:24:12.700 --> 00:24:14.141
Dong Kyung was worried too.

277
00:24:16.841 --> 00:24:18.871
- She was? - All day long.

278
00:24:18.871 --> 00:24:22.210
she talked about her aunt. brother. and Ji Na.

279
00:24:25.851 --> 00:24:29.520
Know something? My motto in life is "Go all in."

280
00:24:32.490 --> 00:24:34.020
Only our faces were the same.

281
00:24:34.821 --> 00:24:36.930
My sister and I had opposite personalities.

282
00:24:38.490 --> 00:24:41.960
It was like she gave me all the bad temper.

283
00:24:43.530 --> 00:24:46.301
She was calm and soft.

284
00:24:49.500 --> 00:24:51.470
When I heard that she had died.

285
00:24:53.010 --> 00:24:55.041
I felt like I lost half of me.

286
00:24:57.811 --> 00:24:59.280
My other half left them to me.

287
00:24:59.280 --> 00:25:00.821
How could I not go all in?

288
00:25:02.381 --> 00:25:04.551
Naturally. I lived for them.

289
00:25:07.391 --> 00:25:08.490
But she...

290
00:25:09.891 --> 00:25:12.291
Dong Kyung was like that ever since she was a child.

291
00:25:12.930 --> 00:25:14.901
She won't tell me if she's struggling.

292
00:25:15.530 --> 00:25:17.170
She always went somewhere and hid.

293
00:25:18.930 --> 00:25:21.101
Then I'd have to go look for her.

294
00:25:22.801 --> 00:25:25.871
Whenever I found her. she was sitting by the sea.

295
00:25:26.240 --> 00:25:27.411
It was heartbreaking.

296
00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:31.381
She acted like she had no home.

297
00:25:40.561 --> 00:25:41.861
I guess she has a home now.

298
00:25:47.901 --> 00:25:49.460
Given how she came back here.

299
00:26:17.391 --> 00:26:19.430
I'm glad she doesn't look like she's in pain.

300
00:26:20.230 --> 00:26:22.401
Her heart is the problem. not her body.

301
00:26:22.730 --> 00:26:23.831
Keep a close eye on her.

302
00:26:24.331 --> 00:26:26.470
You know how good she is at pretending to be okay.

303
00:26:27.270 --> 00:26:29.470
Why is she so good at pretending to be fine?

304
00:26:30.071 --> 00:26:32.470
That was her all her life.

305
00:26:33.581 --> 00:26:35.311
She hates being a burden on other people.

306
00:26:35.311 --> 00:26:36.510
so she's always anxious.

307
00:26:37.551 --> 00:26:39.210
That must be why she came here.

308
00:26:39.210 --> 00:26:40.821
So she wouldn't burden us.

309
00:26:47.161 --> 00:26:48.490
Stop crying.

310
00:26:49.690 --> 00:26:52.361
I'm not crying. The wind is cold. that's why.

311
00:26:53.131 --> 00:26:55.061
I tear up when the wind is cold.

312
00:26:56.200 --> 00:26:57.470
I was born this way.

313
00:27:06.841 --> 00:27:07.881
Hello. Mr. Lee.

314
00:27:09.010 --> 00:27:11.180
Yes. I saw my sister.

315
00:27:12.851 --> 00:27:14.621
I'm sorry for calling out all of a sudden.

316
00:27:16.821 --> 00:27:17.891
The beans?

317
00:27:18.821 --> 00:27:20.291
They're arriving in the morning.

318
00:27:21.490 --> 00:27:23.791
Yes. Good night. boss.

319
00:27:25.061 --> 00:27:27.131
Boss? Do you have a job?

320
00:27:27.460 --> 00:27:29.301
Yes. at a café.

321
00:27:29.301 --> 00:27:30.331
A café?

322
00:27:31.131 --> 00:27:33.000
Every schmo has a café nowadays.

323
00:27:33.770 --> 00:27:36.270
It's always about a guy when you get angry like this.

324
00:27:37.510 --> 00:27:40.071
Remember that guy I said I would kill?

325
00:27:40.611 --> 00:27:42.111
I saw him again recently.

326
00:27:42.381 --> 00:27:43.480
He owns a café.

327
00:27:43.480 --> 00:27:45.851
I'm so jealous. I want to run a café too.

328
00:27:45.851 --> 00:27:47.920
- He wants to get back together. - Oh my gosh.

329
00:27:47.920 --> 00:27:49.520
- So I said okay. - Oh my gosh.

330
00:27:50.121 --> 00:27:51.551
I'm so annoyed.

331
00:27:52.220 --> 00:27:53.220
I wanted to kill him.

332
00:27:53.220 --> 00:27:55.920
but when I saw his smile. my heart just melted.

333
00:27:56.831 --> 00:27:57.960
That's good.

334
00:27:57.960 --> 00:27:59.161
Rage is never good for you.

335
00:27:59.161 --> 00:28:00.430
But the problem is...

336
00:28:00.430 --> 00:28:02.730
there's another guy I want to kill.

337
00:28:02.952 --> 00:28:05.753
- Another guy? - And they know each other.

338
00:28:05.952 --> 00:28:08.253
They even live together. but he didn't tell me.

339
00:28:08.253 --> 00:28:09.853
He was totally toying with me. right?

340
00:28:09.952 --> 00:28:11.192
Gosh. that's confusing.

341
00:28:11.493 --> 00:28:14.932
So you decided to date the guy you originally wanted to kill.

342
00:28:14.932 --> 00:28:17.402
And then. there's another guy you want to kill. Is that it?

343
00:28:17.402 --> 00:28:18.432
Yes.

344
00:28:19.033 --> 00:28:21.303
What? Does it mean you like the guy?

345
00:28:21.702 --> 00:28:23.603
- Which guy? - The second guy.

346
00:28:23.603 --> 00:28:25.573
No. I decided to date the first guy.

347
00:28:26.773 --> 00:28:28.513
Why are you dating the 1st guy when you like the 2nd guy?

348
00:28:29.142 --> 00:28:31.613
You're so stupid. You got low scores on language art. right?

349
00:28:31.613 --> 00:28:33.882
What are you talking about? You're the fool here.

350
00:28:33.882 --> 00:28:36.182
When you like someone. you say you want to kill that guy.

351
00:28:40.392 --> 00:28:43.353
You wanted to kill the first guy. That's in the past tense.

352
00:28:43.353 --> 00:28:46.563
You want to kill the second guy now. That's the present tense.

353
00:28:47.833 --> 00:28:48.833
Gosh.

354
00:28:51.162 --> 00:28:53.402
Stop talking nonsense. And bring the side dishes.

355
00:29:01.543 --> 00:29:02.942
Why isn't this coming off?

356
00:30:29.392 --> 00:30:31.063
Hey. It's snowing!

357
00:30:42.273 --> 00:30:43.442
It's snowing!

358
00:30:44.243 --> 00:30:45.682
It's so beautiful.

359
00:30:46.243 --> 00:30:47.452
Do you want to make a snowman?

360
00:30:47.452 --> 00:30:49.482
Let's make a snowman. I want to make a snowman!

361
00:31:19.843 --> 00:31:23.152
I ran away to this place because I wanted to leave everyone.

362
00:31:23.182 --> 00:31:25.482
But it turned out I wasn't running away.

363
00:31:26.523 --> 00:31:29.122
I thought I ran away from you guys. but once I got here.

364
00:31:29.853 --> 00:31:32.093
I had everything I loved right here.

365
00:31:32.993 --> 00:31:34.033
So...

366
00:31:35.162 --> 00:31:38.132
I really missed all of you.

367
00:31:39.563 --> 00:31:41.672
You need the experience to run away from your family.

368
00:31:42.172 --> 00:31:43.972
You always live your life.

369
00:31:43.972 --> 00:31:46.603
ready to tackle the world. You're never going to be that type.

370
00:31:48.343 --> 00:31:49.972
I can't run away with you.

371
00:31:51.043 --> 00:31:53.783
But I'll always be on your side when you're tackling the world.

372
00:31:57.182 --> 00:31:58.922
By the way. this place looks amazing.

373
00:31:59.182 --> 00:32:01.192
I don't remember the last time I'd been on Jeju Island.

374
00:32:02.093 --> 00:32:05.122
There's no one here because it's a weekday. I love it here.

375
00:32:06.692 --> 00:32:08.932
This is why people love to be freelancers or unemployed.

376
00:32:09.363 --> 00:32:11.363
Let's continue our friendship until our hair turns Gray...

377
00:32:11.363 --> 00:32:14.103
and travel around the world when other people are working.

378
00:32:14.103 --> 00:32:15.902
What? Are you telling me I should be unemployed...

379
00:32:15.902 --> 00:32:17.103
for the rest of my life?

380
00:32:17.103 --> 00:32:18.603
Just spend money like water.

381
00:32:18.603 --> 00:32:20.202
I'll make money like a slave.

382
00:32:24.942 --> 00:32:26.043
Take out your phone.

383
00:32:26.442 --> 00:32:28.382
The weather is amazing. Let's take a photo.

384
00:32:28.853 --> 00:32:29.853
Sure.

385
00:32:32.622 --> 00:32:34.993
All right. You can take the photo.

386
00:32:39.962 --> 00:32:41.263
Let me see.

387
00:32:42.833 --> 00:32:45.563
By the way. what happened the other day?

388
00:32:45.932 --> 00:32:47.833
What do you mean?

389
00:32:47.833 --> 00:32:49.432
You left after getting a call.

390
00:32:50.442 --> 00:32:52.343
Oh. that? It's nothing.

391
00:32:52.343 --> 00:32:54.773
I cursed him out. broke the laptop. and scared him a bit.

392
00:32:55.113 --> 00:32:56.142
What?

393
00:32:56.573 --> 00:32:59.382
That jerk. Jijo King. accused me of plagiarizing his stuff.

394
00:32:59.382 --> 00:33:00.452
What?

395
00:33:01.053 --> 00:33:03.482
It's fine. I handled it.

396
00:33:07.793 --> 00:33:10.053
By the way. the laptop was Mr. Cha's.

397
00:33:12.722 --> 00:33:13.732
Ji Na.

398
00:33:15.432 --> 00:33:17.363
Do you like Mr. Cha?

399
00:33:17.902 --> 00:33:18.902
What?

400
00:33:19.303 --> 00:33:21.902
Do you think I'm crazy? I'm dating Lee Hyun Kyu again.

401
00:33:21.902 --> 00:33:23.972
What? Lee Hyun Kyu? The Lee Hyun Kyu I know?

402
00:33:23.972 --> 00:33:25.073
Do you know what's crazier?

403
00:33:25.073 --> 00:33:26.702
He works at the café on the first floor of your company building.

404
00:33:26.702 --> 00:33:28.343
Who knew he would be so close?

405
00:33:30.142 --> 00:33:32.982
Are you talking about the handsome café owner?

406
00:33:33.442 --> 00:33:36.452
The guy who could be in movies and whose smile lights up the room?

407
00:33:37.652 --> 00:33:39.323
I guess he is handsome.

408
00:33:40.652 --> 00:33:42.222
Ji Na. how are you going to fix this?

409
00:33:42.222 --> 00:33:44.023
You like Mr. Cha.

410
00:33:44.023 --> 00:33:45.622
No. I don't!

411
00:33:50.392 --> 00:33:51.402
It's obvious!

412
00:33:56.103 --> 00:33:57.402
Goodness.

413
00:34:55.732 --> 00:34:56.732
Are you going somewhere?

414
00:34:57.462 --> 00:34:59.363
- I'll see you inside. - Okay.

415
00:35:01.703 --> 00:35:02.902
I'll be back.

416
00:35:03.732 --> 00:35:04.772
Where are you going?

417
00:35:06.203 --> 00:35:07.312
The hospital.

418
00:35:09.113 --> 00:35:11.212
Something happened to her. right?

419
00:35:12.143 --> 00:35:14.752
I won't take long. I'll be back soon. Wait for me.

420
00:35:14.812 --> 00:35:16.183
Let me go with you.

421
00:35:16.513 --> 00:35:17.823
No. You should go first.

422
00:35:18.152 --> 00:35:20.823
I'll leave right after you. I'll be with you.

423
00:35:54.522 --> 00:35:55.593
You're here.

424
00:35:56.453 --> 00:35:57.723
Why didn't you tell me?

425
00:35:58.263 --> 00:35:59.323
I'm okay.

426
00:36:00.422 --> 00:36:03.132
Everything is predetermined.

427
00:36:05.062 --> 00:36:07.832
I remembered why I didn't want to be in love.

428
00:36:09.772 --> 00:36:11.502
Love brings pain.

429
00:36:12.973 --> 00:36:14.772
When your loved ones are gone.

430
00:36:16.143 --> 00:36:17.413
the pain is unbearable.

431
00:36:19.212 --> 00:36:22.082
Creations by humans are indeed great.

432
00:36:23.152 --> 00:36:24.752
Sins and love...

433
00:36:25.582 --> 00:36:27.723
always turn the world upside down.

434
00:36:31.292 --> 00:36:34.232
I shouldn't have fallen in love with anyone.

435
00:36:41.132 --> 00:36:44.272
It's okay. Everything is okay.

436
00:36:46.843 --> 00:36:49.513
I will be born again.

437
00:36:51.743 --> 00:36:53.212
What should I do?

438
00:36:53.513 --> 00:36:55.053
I'm sure you know.

439
00:36:55.953 --> 00:36:57.752
Don't pretend to be clueless. Just tell me.

440
00:36:58.752 --> 00:37:01.422
Deities are meant to live for humanity.

441
00:37:02.522 --> 00:37:05.323
That's the purpose behind their birth.

442
00:37:06.363 --> 00:37:08.363
They live for the people...

443
00:37:08.663 --> 00:37:10.902
and leave the world for the people.

444
00:37:12.933 --> 00:37:14.203
That's our duty.

445
00:38:10.763 --> 00:38:11.893
What are you doing?

446
00:38:13.022 --> 00:38:14.062
Consoling you.

447
00:38:15.393 --> 00:38:17.033
Just like how you consoled me.

448
00:38:36.852 --> 00:38:38.382
Is it bad?

449
00:38:40.252 --> 00:38:42.053
She doesn't have much time left.

450
00:38:44.663 --> 00:38:45.663
It's okay.

451
00:38:46.393 --> 00:38:47.792
This always happened.

452
00:38:49.632 --> 00:38:51.803
Really? What do you want for dinner?

453
00:38:52.502 --> 00:38:53.763
Your dad's calling.

454
00:39:06.143 --> 00:39:07.683
- Sweetheart! - Mom!

455
00:39:07.953 --> 00:39:09.683
Oh. dear.

456
00:39:11.953 --> 00:39:13.922
Thank you. Thank you.

457
00:39:39.482 --> 00:39:40.513
Are you...

458
00:39:41.482 --> 00:39:43.752
- allowed to do that kind of stuff? - No.

459
00:39:44.453 --> 00:39:45.482
What?

460
00:39:45.482 --> 00:39:47.152
I'm not allowed. but I couldn't help it...

461
00:39:48.022 --> 00:39:49.522
because you were watching.

462
00:39:54.292 --> 00:39:56.562
Sometimes. I find myself portraying you in things.

463
00:39:58.527 --> 00:40:01.496
Now that I love you. I sometimes find myself...

464
00:40:02.502 --> 00:40:04.542
pitying humans...

465
00:40:05.602 --> 00:40:06.772
and loving them.

466
00:40:08.113 --> 00:40:10.542
I think I finally understand...

467
00:40:12.666 --> 00:40:14.095
why she loves humans so much.

468
00:40:42.554 --> 00:40:44.963
(Incoming call. Unknown Number)

469
00:40:47.364 --> 00:40:49.864
- Hello? - You're finally picking up.

470
00:40:50.393 --> 00:40:51.904
Dong Kyung. where are you right now?

471
00:40:52.603 --> 00:40:53.733
Mr. Park?

472
00:40:54.204 --> 00:40:55.674
I want you at the office right now.

473
00:40:55.674 --> 00:40:58.444
If you don't come. I'm going to sue Lee Hyun.

474
00:41:02.514 --> 00:41:04.813
Should I keep up what I've been doing?

475
00:41:05.384 --> 00:41:07.284
- Just say the word. - No.

476
00:41:08.083 --> 00:41:09.284
This one's mine.

477
00:41:10.313 --> 00:41:11.454
I'll deal with him myself.

478
00:41:25.963 --> 00:41:27.063
Follow me.

479
00:41:43.683 --> 00:41:45.424
Can you help me just this once?

480
00:41:45.424 --> 00:41:46.554
What are you doing?

481
00:41:46.554 --> 00:41:47.824
Get off me.

482
00:41:47.824 --> 00:41:49.494
Please. I'm dying here.

483
00:41:49.494 --> 00:41:52.594
Will you please let go first?

484
00:41:53.424 --> 00:41:56.393
I mean. now that you and Mr. Cha are both gone.

485
00:41:56.393 --> 00:41:59.404
none of the writers are willing to renew their contracts.

486
00:41:59.404 --> 00:42:01.074
This is really killing me.

487
00:42:01.074 --> 00:42:03.233
Why are you asking me for help?

488
00:42:04.304 --> 00:42:05.503
This is all your fault.

489
00:42:05.904 --> 00:42:08.643
You must've really convinced all those writers...

490
00:42:08.643 --> 00:42:11.344
What? What did you just say?

491
00:42:12.183 --> 00:42:13.213
No. I mean...

492
00:42:14.083 --> 00:42:16.683
You must've worked really hard...

493
00:42:16.683 --> 00:42:17.983
seeing that they're all acting that way.

494
00:42:18.284 --> 00:42:19.853
No one wants to work with a bad guy.

495
00:42:19.853 --> 00:42:21.353
It's like that wherever you go.

496
00:42:21.353 --> 00:42:24.253
- I bet the writers have had enough. - Of course.

497
00:42:24.563 --> 00:42:26.163
I wasn't able to take your side that day...

498
00:42:26.163 --> 00:42:27.694
because I was too flustered.

499
00:42:27.694 --> 00:42:29.963
But I was always on your side.

500
00:42:29.963 --> 00:42:31.333
It's so nice to see you again.

501
00:42:31.804 --> 00:42:33.404
How's your health?

502
00:42:33.404 --> 00:42:34.603
Is everything okay?

503
00:42:34.974 --> 00:42:38.074
I knew he'd get himself in trouble one day.

504
00:42:38.244 --> 00:42:40.603
This is how hard it is to make a living. Dong Kyung.

505
00:42:41.143 --> 00:42:42.614
There are people I need to take care of...

506
00:42:42.614 --> 00:42:44.444
regardless of how much I hate him.

507
00:42:44.444 --> 00:42:46.643
You have no idea how hard it is for me to humour him.

508
00:42:48.353 --> 00:42:50.583
Think of those guys out there.

509
00:42:50.583 --> 00:42:53.083
At this rate. I won't even be able to give them their monthly pay.

510
00:42:53.083 --> 00:42:55.623
If my company goes bankrupt. the same will happen to them.

511
00:42:55.623 --> 00:42:58.264
They're still young. Don't try to ruin their lives. too.

512
00:42:58.663 --> 00:42:59.893
You're right. I'm the bad guy.

513
00:42:59.893 --> 00:43:01.063
Dong Kyung. Dong Kyung.

514
00:43:01.063 --> 00:43:02.463
- My gosh. - Okay.

515
00:43:04.733 --> 00:43:06.804
I'm begging you. Please do me a favour.

516
00:43:08.233 --> 00:43:10.174
Please meet up with Mr. Cha.

517
00:43:10.174 --> 00:43:13.244
Meet up with him just this once and try to convince him.

518
00:43:13.704 --> 00:43:15.014
I get that you can't work here anymore...

519
00:43:15.014 --> 00:43:16.213
because of your health.

520
00:43:16.213 --> 00:43:17.884
But that's not the case for Mr. Cha.

521
00:43:19.983 --> 00:43:21.583
If you refuse to cooperate.

522
00:43:21.583 --> 00:43:23.454
I'll have no choice but to sue Lee Hyun.

523
00:43:23.454 --> 00:43:25.324
Sue her for what?

524
00:43:25.324 --> 00:43:26.884
For damaging our property and obstructing our business.

525
00:43:26.884 --> 00:43:28.154
You know I'm a man who keeps his word. right?

526
00:43:28.154 --> 00:43:29.154
I mean. how...

527
00:43:29.793 --> 00:43:31.264
How do you expect me...

528
00:43:31.264 --> 00:43:32.724
to meet a guy who quit?

529
00:43:32.724 --> 00:43:33.764
Mr. Cha...

530
00:43:37.393 --> 00:43:40.704
Mr. Cha has always been near us.

531
00:43:41.634 --> 00:43:42.634
What?

532
00:43:43.074 --> 00:43:45.744
Up there. That's where he lives.

533
00:43:46.003 --> 00:43:47.143
Mr. Cha...

534
00:43:48.474 --> 00:43:50.014
is the landlord's son.

535
00:43:54.554 --> 00:43:55.683
Can I have some money?

536
00:43:56.554 --> 00:43:58.454
Money? Why?

537
00:43:58.454 --> 00:44:00.384
I got myself in trouble. I need to deal with it.

538
00:44:04.563 --> 00:44:06.463
I didn't buy new golf clubs to beat you with them.

539
00:44:06.463 --> 00:44:07.833
I'll pay you back once I succeed.

540
00:44:07.833 --> 00:44:09.494
How are you going to succeed?

541
00:44:10.893 --> 00:44:12.603
How much are you asking for?

542
00:44:14.404 --> 00:44:15.674
I'm going to start a company.

543
00:44:15.674 --> 00:44:17.474
Why would you start a company?

544
00:44:17.733 --> 00:44:19.704
Then who's going to take care of that building?

545
00:44:19.704 --> 00:44:21.773
I'll continue to take care of it.

546
00:44:21.974 --> 00:44:23.074
The company will be like a hobby for me.

547
00:44:23.074 --> 00:44:25.444
You punk. Who starts a company for fun?

548
00:44:25.444 --> 00:44:27.413
It won't be as expensive as your hobby.

549
00:44:27.583 --> 00:44:28.713
and it'll surely make more money.

550
00:44:28.713 --> 00:44:30.654
You never lose an argument.

551
00:44:32.784 --> 00:44:34.123
How much are you going to pay in interest?

552
00:44:34.123 --> 00:44:36.054
Why would you ask your own son for interest?

553
00:44:36.054 --> 00:44:37.924
Then ask the bank for money.

554
00:44:38.123 --> 00:44:39.463
Okay. fine.

555
00:44:39.463 --> 00:44:42.134
I'll pay you enough interest.

556
00:44:42.563 --> 00:44:43.893
Now we're talking.

557
00:44:46.634 --> 00:44:48.804
If only you were as good of a businessman as Hyun Kyu...

558
00:44:49.304 --> 00:44:52.204
By the way. why did he behave like that on that day?

559
00:44:52.503 --> 00:44:54.244
- What day? - The day he suddenly...

560
00:44:54.244 --> 00:44:56.373
hugged me and called me "Dad".

561
00:44:56.574 --> 00:44:59.043
Oh. he did it to protect me.

562
00:44:59.284 --> 00:45:00.284
My gosh.

563
00:45:01.683 --> 00:45:03.253
Having taken care of him must be paying off.

564
00:45:03.983 --> 00:45:05.853
I shouldn't have taken such good care of him

565
00:45:05.853 --> 00:45:06.884
Why?

566
00:45:06.884 --> 00:45:09.094
Is he rude to you now that he's all grown up?

567
00:45:09.494 --> 00:45:10.494
Well...

568
00:45:11.793 --> 00:45:12.963
He doesn't make things easy.

569
00:45:14.793 --> 00:45:17.233
That means he's ready to compete with you.

570
00:45:20.563 --> 00:45:21.674
Go ahead.

571
00:45:23.534 --> 00:45:26.344
(Tak Dong Kyung)

572
00:45:33.884 --> 00:45:34.954
Welcome.

573
00:45:37.114 --> 00:45:38.284
Unbelievable.

574
00:45:57.984 --> 00:45:59.885
So this is why you always came to work early...

575
00:45:59.885 --> 00:46:01.925
and went home late.

576
00:46:04.254 --> 00:46:06.394
Are you talking to yourself. or are you omitting honorifics now?

577
00:46:08.294 --> 00:46:10.394
I must say. this is a scary world.

578
00:46:10.995 --> 00:46:13.104
I guess I really can't trust anyone.

579
00:46:13.104 --> 00:46:15.374
This time. I can tell you're just omitting honorifics.

580
00:46:17.475 --> 00:46:18.805
Are you really the landlord?

581
00:46:18.805 --> 00:46:20.374
No. not me. My dad is.

582
00:46:22.175 --> 00:46:25.385
Then is the sports car parked in the basement...

583
00:46:25.385 --> 00:46:27.314
- also yours? - Yes.

584
00:46:30.314 --> 00:46:33.984
Does your father own buildings other than this one?

585
00:46:34.484 --> 00:46:35.495
Yes.

586
00:46:36.155 --> 00:46:37.425
This is the smallest one.

587
00:46:37.425 --> 00:46:39.164
My brother and dad manage the rest.

588
00:46:39.465 --> 00:46:41.664
If you're the landlord's son.

589
00:46:41.664 --> 00:46:43.635
why did you work for a company that pays so little?

590
00:46:43.635 --> 00:46:45.104
Because it was close to home.

591
00:46:47.035 --> 00:46:48.334
How clever.

592
00:46:51.604 --> 00:46:53.245
Why did you quit in the first place?

593
00:46:54.087 --> 00:46:56.757
The same reason as yours. I couldn't take it.

594
00:46:57.127 --> 00:46:58.396
You've been good at taking it.

595
00:47:00.826 --> 00:47:01.896
You're right.

596
00:47:03.027 --> 00:47:04.467
But I can't these days.

597
00:47:05.337 --> 00:47:08.206
Why not? Because Mr. Park criticized Ji Na?

598
00:47:09.366 --> 00:47:11.337
She told me everything.

599
00:47:11.976 --> 00:47:13.177
I doubt she told you everything.

600
00:47:15.246 --> 00:47:17.476
I guess there really was something as I suspected.

601
00:47:17.476 --> 00:47:19.616
I guess she told you enough for you to suspect it.

602
00:47:20.116 --> 00:47:22.587
So? What do you plan to do?

603
00:47:22.587 --> 00:47:23.746
I'm going to start a company.

604
00:47:24.956 --> 00:47:26.456
That's why I wanted to see you.

605
00:47:27.786 --> 00:47:30.087
Recover quickly.

606
00:47:30.456 --> 00:47:32.556
I'll make you a team leader if you come to me.

607
00:47:35.996 --> 00:47:37.527
That wasn't my question.

608
00:47:40.436 --> 00:47:42.337
Forget it.

609
00:47:42.507 --> 00:47:46.476
Furthermore. I'm going to demand an insanely high salary.

610
00:47:47.206 --> 00:47:49.806
I'll just give you a higher title. How about director?

611
00:47:49.806 --> 00:47:51.976
No. thanks. I want a high salary.

612
00:47:52.616 --> 00:47:54.116
What's your current salary?

613
00:47:55.047 --> 00:47:57.846
- I'm sorry. - It's okay.

614
00:47:57.846 --> 00:47:59.416
You had your reasons.

615
00:47:59.916 --> 00:48:01.857
I'll work even harder.

616
00:48:02.286 --> 00:48:04.357
Is your sister doing better?

617
00:48:05.726 --> 00:48:06.757
No.

618
00:48:07.197 --> 00:48:08.927
But she will.

619
00:48:09.797 --> 00:48:10.866
I'm sure.

620
00:48:14.596 --> 00:48:15.637
Sis.

621
00:48:18.706 --> 00:48:21.277
Are you Sun Kyung's sister?

622
00:48:21.646 --> 00:48:22.746
I saw you several times before.

623
00:48:23.576 --> 00:48:25.846
Why are you here? Did you come to see me?

624
00:48:26.476 --> 00:48:27.777
I'm working hard.

625
00:48:27.777 --> 00:48:29.487
He's a very good worker.

626
00:48:29.487 --> 00:48:30.916
He works hard and...

627
00:48:30.916 --> 00:48:34.556
It's fine. I was just passing by and dropped in.

628
00:48:34.726 --> 00:48:36.587
I was just passing by.

629
00:48:36.587 --> 00:48:39.496
Okay. Would you like some coffee? On the house.

630
00:48:39.496 --> 00:48:41.627
Sure. Yes. please. Thank you.

631
00:48:44.866 --> 00:48:47.737
Why didn't I realize?

632
00:48:49.806 --> 00:48:50.806
Pardon?

633
00:48:51.337 --> 00:48:52.576
What? Nothing.

634
00:48:52.936 --> 00:48:57.177
I was wondering why I didn't realize...

635
00:48:57.177 --> 00:48:58.976
how nice this café was.

636
00:49:01.177 --> 00:49:02.217
What is it?

637
00:49:04.646 --> 00:49:07.016
Here's your coffee. You like iced Americano. right?

638
00:49:07.016 --> 00:49:08.127
You always got that.

639
00:49:08.786 --> 00:49:10.786
You have a good memory.

640
00:49:13.226 --> 00:49:14.297
Oh my.

641
00:49:15.127 --> 00:49:18.096
Coffee made by people who studied abroad tastes different.

642
00:49:18.567 --> 00:49:22.237
How did you know I studied abroad?

643
00:49:23.206 --> 00:49:25.777
It smelled. I smell a runaway.

644
00:49:26.237 --> 00:49:28.507
Oh dear. My mistake.

645
00:49:28.646 --> 00:49:29.846
The coffee scents.

646
00:49:30.076 --> 00:49:31.076
What's wrong with you?

647
00:49:31.777 --> 00:49:34.217
Do you feel sick? Do you need a doctor?

648
00:49:34.616 --> 00:49:36.447
Are you confusing your words?

649
00:49:36.447 --> 00:49:38.286
I'm not sick. I'm fine.

650
00:49:38.887 --> 00:49:41.056
The coffee woke me right up.

651
00:49:41.186 --> 00:49:44.627
I heard that you used to swim.

652
00:49:45.726 --> 00:49:48.297
Where did you hear about that?

653
00:49:48.527 --> 00:49:50.967
Just from people who heard from people.

654
00:49:52.737 --> 00:49:55.107
It wasn't me. I didn't tell her.

655
00:49:55.837 --> 00:49:58.976
If you swim. are you good at submerging too?

656
00:50:00.337 --> 00:50:03.476
Well... It's probably easier for me than regular people.

657
00:50:04.246 --> 00:50:05.476
It's easier.

658
00:50:06.217 --> 00:50:09.186
That must be why it's easy for you to submerge and disappear.

659
00:50:09.987 --> 00:50:11.016
Pardon?

660
00:50:11.317 --> 00:50:12.456
What do you think...

661
00:50:12.456 --> 00:50:14.786
about people who ghost girlfriends to break up with them?

662
00:50:16.627 --> 00:50:17.956
I think...

663
00:50:18.456 --> 00:50:21.527
they are cowards...

664
00:50:21.627 --> 00:50:24.067
Right? It's totally cowardly. isn't it?

665
00:50:24.496 --> 00:50:27.766
Why do people do something so cowardly?

666
00:50:29.206 --> 00:50:30.206
What's wrong with you?

667
00:50:30.936 --> 00:50:32.137
Did Myul Mang ghost you?

668
00:50:32.637 --> 00:50:33.637
No.

669
00:50:36.947 --> 00:50:40.416
I was just passing by...

670
00:50:40.416 --> 00:50:42.016
and dropped in.

671
00:50:42.317 --> 00:50:43.616
so I'll go now.

672
00:50:44.746 --> 00:50:45.786
What's wrong with you?

673
00:50:46.317 --> 00:50:47.387
Why did you come?

674
00:50:47.387 --> 00:50:49.556
Are you leaving? I'll see you again.

675
00:50:54.456 --> 00:50:55.496
What's wrong with her?

676
00:50:59.366 --> 00:51:01.297
Your sister seems fine.

677
00:51:02.266 --> 00:51:03.306
Sure.

678
00:51:07.436 --> 00:51:10.277
Ji Na. All you care about is looks.

679
00:51:20.956 --> 00:51:23.826
I am stopping the series for personal reasons.

680
00:51:24.326 --> 00:51:27.797
I'd like to thank all the viewers who read my story. flaws and all.

681
00:51:27.996 --> 00:51:30.697
I'll see you again with a new story.

682
00:51:31.427 --> 00:51:32.896
(Notice of Termination of Series)

683
00:51:37.536 --> 00:51:39.277
I read all of your novels.

684
00:51:39.277 --> 00:51:41.107
And you need one thing.

685
00:51:41.607 --> 00:51:42.677
A new male character.

686
00:51:44.076 --> 00:51:45.677
A new male character.

687
00:52:02.567 --> 00:52:03.697
(Who said)

688
00:52:03.697 --> 00:52:06.896
Who said first loves never work out?

689
00:52:08.237 --> 00:52:10.266
Ji Woo was overcome with the desire...

690
00:52:10.266 --> 00:52:12.507
to find the person who said that and kill him.

691
00:52:13.777 --> 00:52:17.277
Although it wasn't his fault that her love failed.

692
00:52:17.507 --> 00:52:19.116
that was what she wanted to do.

693
00:52:20.076 --> 00:52:22.987
Because she couldn't kill her first love.

694
00:52:24.217 --> 00:52:25.357
But then again.

695
00:52:25.357 --> 00:52:28.157
she may not have the energy to kill him even if she met him.

696
00:52:29.387 --> 00:52:31.956
Ji Woo was sitting. crying. in front of her first love's home...

697
00:52:31.956 --> 00:52:33.326
for three hours.

698
00:52:33.326 --> 00:52:36.197
(For three hours)

699
00:52:36.197 --> 00:52:37.266
I can't.

700
00:52:38.936 --> 00:52:42.007
"What?" The unfamiliar voice made her look up.

701
00:52:42.407 --> 00:52:44.936
and a man with an equally unfamiliar face...

702
00:52:44.936 --> 00:52:46.337
was standing in front of her.

703
00:52:47.476 --> 00:52:49.607
The man that she saw with her blurred vision...

704
00:52:49.607 --> 00:52:51.407
distorted by the rain and tears...

705
00:52:51.817 --> 00:52:55.686
showed no emotion on his face and simply looked down at her.

706
00:52:56.516 --> 00:52:58.857
I can't go in if you sit there like that.

707
00:53:02.186 --> 00:53:03.826
Her first kiss with the man she first met...

708
00:53:03.826 --> 00:53:05.257
tasted like a rain shower.

709
00:53:09.996 --> 00:53:12.067
Ji Woo knew right then and there.

710
00:53:12.967 --> 00:53:14.166
"I won't be able"...

711
00:53:15.036 --> 00:53:16.607
"to avoid him"...

712
00:53:17.766 --> 00:53:19.407
"or loving him."

713
00:53:33.056 --> 00:53:35.326
Yes. I'm almost home.

714
00:53:35.326 --> 00:53:36.726
Are you home?

715
00:53:40.683 --> 00:53:41.853
No.

716
00:53:42.527 --> 00:53:46.166
I was able to hold back and didn't commit murder.

717
00:53:49.837 --> 00:53:50.907
My aunt?

718
00:53:51.407 --> 00:53:54.507
She said she had to go somewhere. so she isn't coming over.

719
00:54:02.916 --> 00:54:03.916
Really?

720
00:54:11.127 --> 00:54:12.127
Seriously.

721
00:54:19.797 --> 00:54:22.507
This reminds me of old times.

722
00:54:23.107 --> 00:54:24.206
It wasn't that long ago.

723
00:54:24.637 --> 00:54:26.137
It was quite recent.

724
00:54:27.677 --> 00:54:31.447
Your problem is that you nitpick about everything I say.

725
00:54:31.447 --> 00:54:33.377
You are such a mood killer.

726
00:54:33.777 --> 00:54:36.317
I'm not nitpicking. I'm pointing out the truth.

727
00:54:38.587 --> 00:54:41.487
You haven't changed. Not at all.

728
00:54:41.956 --> 00:54:44.056
You were a real jerk back then too.

729
00:54:45.056 --> 00:54:46.927
Why was I a jerk?

730
00:54:46.927 --> 00:54:48.627
For a bunch of reasons.

731
00:54:49.266 --> 00:54:51.627
But you were cute every once in a while.

732
00:54:53.297 --> 00:54:55.567
Cute? Me?

733
00:54:57.306 --> 00:55:00.507
I know you turned off the lights for me that night.

734
00:55:19.927 --> 00:55:21.527
I always thought...

735
00:55:21.896 --> 00:55:25.936
the darkness was scary and frightening.

736
00:55:26.237 --> 00:55:27.666
But for the first time.

737
00:55:28.237 --> 00:55:31.237
I realized that sometimes. kindness and consideration...

738
00:55:31.237 --> 00:55:33.206
are dark.

739
00:55:37.306 --> 00:55:38.306
You're wrong.

740
00:55:39.016 --> 00:55:40.576
I turned them off because I liked the dark.

741
00:55:40.576 --> 00:55:43.646
Hey. I said to stop killing the mood.

742
00:55:53.996 --> 00:55:55.996
You're not even reading.

743
00:55:56.467 --> 00:55:57.927
I flipped the page.

744
00:55:57.927 --> 00:55:59.096
You're not reading. are you?

745
00:56:01.936 --> 00:56:02.967
Want one?

746
00:56:03.337 --> 00:56:04.936
I don't eat.

747
00:56:07.637 --> 00:56:08.806
You pretend to though.

748
00:56:09.177 --> 00:56:10.746
- Want me to play along? - Yes.

749
00:56:12.447 --> 00:56:14.516
There's no one by that name.

750
00:56:15.286 --> 00:56:16.916
That can't be.

751
00:56:17.317 --> 00:56:20.657
I met with that doctor just a few days ago.

752
00:56:22.786 --> 00:56:25.297
This is the list of neurosurgeons...

753
00:56:25.297 --> 00:56:26.726
at our hospital.

754
00:56:27.527 --> 00:56:29.826
Why isn't he on this list?

755
00:56:30.627 --> 00:56:32.337
I'm positive.

756
00:56:32.337 --> 00:56:34.936
My niece and I met with Dr. Lee Yoon Ho.

757
00:56:35.467 --> 00:56:39.507
He said she was on the list of patients for the new drug.

758
00:56:39.936 --> 00:56:42.306
You seem to be mistaken.

759
00:56:42.306 --> 00:56:45.146
Why don't you talk to your niece?

760
00:56:45.146 --> 00:56:47.277
That can't be.

761
00:56:47.277 --> 00:56:49.846
I'm positive I spoke with him.

762
00:56:49.846 --> 00:56:51.016
Soo. what's wrong?

763
00:56:51.416 --> 00:56:52.516
I apologize.

764
00:56:52.516 --> 00:56:55.056
Right now. there's nothing I can do for you.

765
00:56:56.427 --> 00:56:57.527
What...

766
00:57:00.257 --> 00:57:01.297
What?

767
00:57:01.797 --> 00:57:03.197
That's not possible.

768
00:57:03.797 --> 00:57:05.266
I definitely talked to him.

769
00:57:05.266 --> 00:57:06.436
Why isn't he here?

770
00:57:09.007 --> 00:57:11.866
Kevin. something is off.

771
00:57:12.476 --> 00:57:13.607
I definitely...

772
00:57:14.436 --> 00:57:17.107
I definitely saw him and talked to him here.

773
00:57:18.107 --> 00:57:19.217
But how...

774
00:57:19.916 --> 00:57:23.186
My gosh. That ghost must have been sighted again.

775
00:57:25.016 --> 00:57:26.056
Excuse me?

776
00:57:26.516 --> 00:57:28.456
There's a ghost roaming around this hospital.

777
00:57:29.427 --> 00:57:31.657
- A ghost? - Yes.

778
00:57:32.027 --> 00:57:33.857
This rumour has been going around for several years.

779
00:57:34.257 --> 00:57:36.427
A lot of people had seen that doctor.

780
00:57:36.866 --> 00:57:38.896
My guess is that people here are exhausted.

781
00:57:38.896 --> 00:57:40.536
so it's easier to get bewitched by the ghost.

782
00:57:41.067 --> 00:57:43.237
You should look for another hospital.

783
00:57:43.237 --> 00:57:44.507
But I have no choice now.

784
00:57:45.067 --> 00:57:46.806
What are you talking about? A ghost?

785
00:57:48.237 --> 00:57:49.976
That's ridiculous.

786
00:57:50.346 --> 00:57:52.877
If that's not it. you must've been conned.

787
00:57:53.416 --> 00:57:55.746
So if you're the one who's been deceived.

788
00:57:55.746 --> 00:57:57.616
those two must have been in on it together.

789
00:57:58.516 --> 00:57:59.686
But you said she's your niece.

790
00:57:59.987 --> 00:58:01.616
Why would she want to deceive you?

791
00:58:03.157 --> 00:58:06.226
But is that possible to pull off at a big hospital like this?

792
00:58:06.896 --> 00:58:09.127
The security guards must be watching.

793
00:58:09.996 --> 00:58:12.067
Gosh. I'm telling you. It must've been the ghost.

794
00:58:18.467 --> 00:58:19.576
Gosh.

795
00:58:26.277 --> 00:58:27.717
What's wrong?

796
00:58:27.717 --> 00:58:29.887
- What's wrong with you? - Doctor.

797
00:58:30.246 --> 00:58:31.987
Doctor! We need help over here.

798
00:58:32.916 --> 00:58:34.487
- What's wrong? - Are you okay?

799
00:58:37.826 --> 00:58:41.157
I love this place because the moon is so big and bright.

800
00:58:42.627 --> 00:58:45.027
- When it's the same moon. - Right.

801
00:58:46.036 --> 00:58:47.396
Even when it's the same moon.

802
00:58:47.396 --> 00:58:50.907
it looks a lot more beautiful from here.

803
00:58:54.877 --> 00:58:56.476
If I were to be born again.

804
00:58:57.226 --> 00:58:59.566
I want to be born as a moon like that.

805
00:59:02.717 --> 00:59:06.357
You know. inanimate things like the sun. moon. stars. and wind.

806
00:59:07.387 --> 00:59:09.987
They just exist instead of living.

807
00:59:11.657 --> 00:59:13.456
I want to be one of those things in my next life.

808
00:59:19.137 --> 00:59:20.797
Then. what would you be if you could go back?

809
00:59:22.306 --> 00:59:23.967
If you could go back in time?

810
00:59:29.146 --> 00:59:31.646
- I'm not sure. - Even if I go back in time.

811
00:59:33.217 --> 00:59:34.616
I'll make the same decision.

812
00:59:36.087 --> 00:59:37.487
Meeting you.

813
00:59:37.987 --> 00:59:39.186
falling in love with you.

814
00:59:40.016 --> 00:59:42.556
and walking out here like this.

815
00:59:47.857 --> 00:59:50.226
I know. You probably won't make the same decision.

816
00:59:57.137 --> 00:59:58.407
I don't have any regrets.

817
01:00:02.907 --> 01:00:05.007
My world changed after getting to know you.

818
01:00:11.246 --> 01:00:12.387
This...

819
01:00:13.257 --> 01:00:15.556
I got this from the girl at the hospital.

820
01:00:16.987 --> 01:00:20.496
She said everything inside this depends on my love.

821
01:00:21.226 --> 01:00:23.197
She asked me if I was scared.

822
01:00:27.436 --> 01:00:28.666
I was scared.

823
01:00:29.907 --> 01:00:30.967
But...

824
01:00:33.936 --> 01:00:35.377
I'm not scared anymore.

825
01:00:47.817 --> 01:00:50.527
I'm not scared.

826
01:00:52.297 --> 01:00:53.326
Not anymore.

827
01:01:06.536 --> 01:01:07.576
Hello?

828
01:01:20.516 --> 01:01:21.556
Aunt!

829
01:01:23.826 --> 01:01:26.157
I'm fine. Don't make a fuss.

830
01:01:26.627 --> 01:01:28.996
It was a stress-induced stomach cramp.

831
01:01:28.996 --> 01:01:31.067
A stomach cramp? Does it hurt a lot?

832
01:01:31.366 --> 01:01:33.237
Should I go outside and buy you some porridge?

833
01:01:33.596 --> 01:01:35.297
Kevin didn't have any food either. right?

834
01:01:43.277 --> 01:01:44.277
Tak Dong Kyung.

835
01:01:46.217 --> 01:01:47.246
Yes?

836
01:01:47.576 --> 01:01:49.346
I came to the hospital...

837
01:01:50.717 --> 01:01:52.456
and heard something that didn't add up.

838
01:01:54.786 --> 01:01:57.157
- Okay. - I want you to explain it.

839
01:01:58.286 --> 01:02:01.657
I came back to meet with the doctor we met the other day.

840
01:02:03.866 --> 01:02:06.197
But I was informed there was no such doctor here.

841
01:02:08.766 --> 01:02:09.806
Then.

842
01:02:10.507 --> 01:02:13.777
everything the doctor told me cannot be true.

843
01:02:14.607 --> 01:02:17.407
- Well. Aunt... - I don't want to hear it.

844
01:02:17.407 --> 01:02:19.447
Don't argue with me. Let's get you admitted.

845
01:02:19.947 --> 01:02:21.846
Kevin will look for a new hospital.

846
01:02:22.916 --> 01:02:23.987
Aunt.

847
01:02:24.087 --> 01:02:26.157
The new hospital will be as good as this one.

848
01:02:26.916 --> 01:02:29.186
We already booked an appointment. Go get admitted there.

849
01:02:29.186 --> 01:02:30.786
- And get all the exams. - Aunt.

850
01:02:34.527 --> 01:02:35.527
I will...

851
01:02:38.096 --> 01:02:40.396
die even if I stay in the hospital.

852
01:02:43.137 --> 01:02:44.907
How could you say that to me now?

853
01:02:45.706 --> 01:02:46.737
I will...

854
01:02:50.476 --> 01:02:51.777
die...

855
01:02:53.146 --> 01:02:54.377
even if I get the surgery.

856
01:02:57.686 --> 01:02:58.717
Why...

857
01:03:00.186 --> 01:03:01.357
Why are you dying?

858
01:03:02.217 --> 01:03:04.627
- Why are you dying? - Soo. take it easy.

859
01:03:06.996 --> 01:03:10.127
Let's get you admitted to this hospital right now.

860
01:03:14.596 --> 01:03:17.766
Please. Let's get you treated. Dong Kyung. Please?

861
01:03:18.366 --> 01:03:19.436
Stay in the hospital.

862
01:03:20.337 --> 01:03:22.507
You must get admitted now!

863
01:03:24.576 --> 01:03:26.717
- Aunt. Aunt... - My gosh.

864
01:03:28.377 --> 01:03:29.547
Are you okay?

865
01:03:30.516 --> 01:03:31.616
Doctor!

866
01:03:32.087 --> 01:03:34.516
Dong Kyung. please get admitted.

867
01:03:35.657 --> 01:03:37.226
Let me check her first.

868
01:03:38.127 --> 01:03:39.197
Aunt.

869
01:03:46.197 --> 01:03:47.797
Right now. Soo needs...

870
01:03:48.567 --> 01:03:50.666
to be stable.

871
01:03:51.637 --> 01:03:53.337
Soo and Dong Kyung...

872
01:03:54.536 --> 01:03:58.507
If you guys stay together. it won't be good.

873
01:04:00.476 --> 01:04:01.576
Just...

874
01:04:01.916 --> 01:04:03.616
Maybe. you should go somewhere and wait until she calms down.

875
01:04:03.616 --> 01:04:05.217
And then. I'll call you. Okay?

876
01:04:06.516 --> 01:04:07.887
I'm sorry. Dong Kyung.

877
01:04:18.527 --> 01:04:20.737
(Registration. Payment. Admittance and Discharge)

878
01:05:36.746 --> 01:05:37.907
This is way too hard.

879
01:05:42.932 --> 01:05:44.232
Please help me.

880
01:05:45.087 --> 01:05:46.487
Help me.

881
01:05:48.726 --> 01:05:50.626
I don't know what to do.

882
01:05:51.157 --> 01:05:52.596
There's no way to explain...

883
01:05:52.596 --> 01:05:55.127
that I will die no matter what I try.

884
01:05:55.527 --> 01:05:58.826
If I didn't know that... If I didn't know that would be my fate...

885
01:05:58.826 --> 01:05:59.936
I'll help you.

886
01:06:04.166 --> 01:06:05.737
Will you let me live?

887
01:06:06.806 --> 01:06:07.837
No.

888
01:06:08.837 --> 01:06:10.547
I can't do that.

889
01:06:11.576 --> 01:06:13.346
That is your fate.

890
01:06:16.387 --> 01:06:17.447
But...

891
01:06:19.987 --> 01:06:22.657
I can change his fate and yours a bit.

892
01:06:24.857 --> 01:06:27.226
I can remove you from his fate. and vice versa.

893
01:06:27.826 --> 01:06:29.297
As if you had never met.

894
01:06:33.596 --> 01:06:35.637
Then. you will die as fated...

895
01:06:36.206 --> 01:06:38.137
without knowing anything.

896
01:06:38.607 --> 01:06:41.476
Like any other patient. you'll get treated and try to get better.

897
01:06:42.277 --> 01:06:44.677
You will slowly face your death.

898
01:06:45.846 --> 01:06:48.416
You won't remember each other. and the contract will be void.

899
01:06:51.087 --> 01:06:52.657
But instead. your choice...

900
01:06:53.956 --> 01:06:57.326
won't make the world collapse or bring death to the one you love.

901
01:07:03.127 --> 01:07:04.326
Will you choose to do that?

902
01:07:12.907 --> 01:07:14.377
There's not much time.

903
01:07:15.536 --> 01:07:16.576
Hurry.

904
01:07:17.446 --> 01:07:18.946
You need to make a choice.

905
01:08:51.267 --> 01:08:54.106
(Doom At Your Service)

906
01:08:55.137 --> 01:08:56.977
I don't remember much.

907
01:08:57.547 --> 01:08:58.706
It comes with the illness.

908
01:08:59.477 --> 01:09:00.816
She knows nothing.

909
01:09:02.517 --> 01:09:04.486
I want a clear answer.

910
01:09:04.916 --> 01:09:07.456
- Will you take? - Or forget?

911
01:09:07.456 --> 01:09:08.717
Or love on your own.

912
01:09:09.526 --> 01:09:10.627
Dong Kyung.

913
01:09:12.956 --> 01:09:15.757
Tell me what you did to me.

914
01:09:16.326 --> 01:09:19.297
I didn't do anything to you. I did something to her.

915
01:09:19.437 --> 01:09:20.536
Help me.

916
01:09:23.066 --> 01:09:24.406
Who are you?

916
01:09:25.305 --> 01:10:25.924
